146
00:06:06,190 --> 00:06:06,950
Come on.

147
00:06:07,870 --> 00:06:08,310
Mm.

148
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:19,750
When are you going back to school?

149
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:21,360
Tomorrow.

150
00:06:22,390 --> 00:06:23,390
When is your flight?

151
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:25,800
At twenty past eight.

152
00:06:25,950 --> 00:06:27,630
What a coincidence.
That's also my flight.

153
00:06:28,270 --> 00:06:29,630
How about you go together?

154
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:31,040
Oh.

155
00:06:36,630 --> 00:06:37,190
Hey.

156
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:37,950
Huh?

157
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,750
Take it back, Zhizhi.

158
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:45,630
Why do you always call me that?

159
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:46,950
Because you said

160
00:06:47,190 --> 00:06:49,190
only those close to you
could call you that.

161
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:52,920
Jiaxu,

162
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:54,800
when you see Qian Fei get married,

163
00:06:54,950 --> 00:06:55,920
do you also want

164
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:57,390
a girlfriend?

165
00:06:57,390 --> 00:06:59,360
Why do you keep asking me
to get a girlfriend

166
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:00,800
or have a blind date?

167
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,560
I'm just 25.

168
00:07:03,070 --> 00:07:03,870
Be patient, please.

169
00:07:04,270 --> 00:07:05,750
Then, when will you have a girlfriend?

170
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:08,190
Even my brother has a pursuer.

171
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:18,310
If you're all alone,

172
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:20,830
nobody will look after you
when you're sick.

173
00:07:27,870 --> 00:07:29,310
Don't be upset.

174
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:31,560
I just don't want you to be alone.

175
00:07:31,950 --> 00:07:33,390
Fine, I won't bring it up again.

176
00:07:38,310 --> 00:07:38,870
Oh.

177
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:40,830
How old are you?

178
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:43,040
I'll turn 19 after this year's birthday.

179
00:07:46,390 --> 00:07:47,920
Not until you're 20.

180
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:04,600
Thanks, Jiaxu.

181
00:08:05,510 --> 00:08:06,800
The flight leaves tomorrow morning.

182
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,000
Go to bed early.

183
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:09,950
I should go home.

184
00:08:10,070 --> 00:08:10,870
Okay.

185
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:13,600
Zhizhi.

186
00:08:13,950 --> 00:08:14,240
Huh?

187
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:20,040
New-year present for you.

188
00:08:27,390 --> 00:08:28,190
Take it.

189
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:34,960
Go back.

190
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:37,630
Thank you.

191
00:08:39,020 --> 00:08:44,110
♪If the dark clouds hadn't floated past♪

192
00:08:44,460 --> 00:08:47,950
♪How could I crash-land♪

193
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:52,510
♪On your planet?♪

194
00:08:53,050 --> 00:08:57,100
♪As the sun set,
